Refactor to enhance readability and maintainability
Consolidated prompt structure and removed duplicate logic. Descriptive text is now saved to a file and detailed messages are provided for reported inconsistencies.

Remove redundant code and optimize report generation
Removed redundant prompt instructions and unused variables in `US_USM.py`. Added functionality to save descriptions text to a file on the desktop and provided checks to manage "Area non trovata" in stratigraphic relationships. This improves code readability and functionality.

Update metadata version to 4.8.4
Updated to version 4.8.4 to include improvements in code readability and functionality. Changes include removing redundant instructions and unused variables, adding functionality for saving descriptions to a file, and managing errors in stratigraphic relationships.

Add user authentication module
Implement the authentication module to manage user login and registration. This includes basic validation, session handling, and user data encryption. This feature is crucial for ensuring secure access to the application.

Refactor imports and add ThesaurusStyler for layer styling
Refactored import statements for better clarity and modularity. Introduced the ThesaurusStyler class to apply consistent styles to layers based on thesaurus data, improving map visualization. Enhanced data handling and query mechanisms for both SQLite and PostgreSQL databases.

Update map preview method in US_USM.py
Renamed the loadMapPreview method to loadMapPreview_new to improve consistency with the updated function definitions in pyQGIS. This change ensures the correct loading and visualization of data layers on the map canvas.
